        public static <NodeT,X extends java.lang.Exception> java.lang.String toString(NodeT root,
                                                                              IMeshWalker<NodeT,X> walker,
                                                                              java.util.Optional<IIdProvider<java.lang.Integer,NodeT>> optionalIdProvider)
                                                                       throws X extends java.lang.Exception
        Returns a string representation of the graph. The individual nodes are represented using their toString() method. This is useful for debugging.
        Parameters:
        root - the root node of the graph to visualize.
        walker - the mesh walker used to traverse the graph.
        optionalIdProvider - an optional IdProvider that provides integer IDs for all Nodes. If it is empty, we will use an IdManager. The Ids are assumed to be stable (the same on each query of the same node).
        Throws:
        X extends java.lang.Exception

      • toShortString

        public static <NodeT,X extends java.lang.Exception> java.lang.String toShortString(NodeT root,
                                                                                   IMeshWalker<NodeT,X> walker,
                                                                                   java.util.Optional<IIdProvider<java.lang.Integer,NodeT>> optionalIdProvider)
                                                                            throws X extends java.lang.Exception
        Returns a human-readable string representation of the graph. The individual nodes are only represented as integers. This is useful for debugging.
        Parameters:
        root - the root node of the graph to visualize.
        walker - the mesh walker used to traverse the graph.
        optionalIdProvider - an optional IdProvider that provides integer IDs for all Nodes. If it is empty, we will use an IdManager. The Ids are assumed to be stable (the same on each query of the same node).
        Throws:
        X extends java.lang.Exception
